commit_message:
Don't pull pysendfile from googlecode

pysendfile is already in test-requirements and in global requirements.
Explicitly setting a dependency on an external domain results in a
blocked gate whenever that domain changes something.

http://pysendfile.googlecode.com/files/pysendfile-2.0.0.tar.gz is now
returning 404 errors.

Fixes-Bug: #1315062
Change-Id: Ie2b6598b57be2bc62a74a199b03069cd19810461

Increase length of 'name' column in package table

When using mysql, we need to make sure that the
name column is long enough to accomodate the
package name.

'io.murano.lib.networks.Neutron' is more than
20 chars.  Modify the schema to make it 80 chars

commit_message:
Fix ceilometer-acompute rejoin problems

The problem was in the screenrc file generated, where the
following command appeared:

sg libvirtd "ceilometer-agent-compute
                 --config-file /etc/ceilometer/ceilometer.conf"^M"

The final "^M" was not then parsed.

Change-Id: Ie6c5b1c9e3d196a3a9c343c2afb46435711c10f5
Closes-bug: #1311666

commit_message:
xenapi: fixup agent tests

The root cause of the slow agent tests was not mocking this method:
compute_utils.add_instance_fault_from_exc

This cleans up the tests to share a bit more code, and ensures they
actually check that the appropriate exception is raised.

This change adds a log message to report errors that could occur in
running systems that also helped identify this issue in the unit tests.

test_spawn_fails_agent_not_implemented was a duplicate test and has been
removed.

Change-Id: I6fd31520fffd5e888ce0c2b58af2715f0d929ce1
Closes-Bug: #1279317

revisions:
[{'number': 8, 'created': '2014-05-01 07:08:27.000000000', 'files': ['heat/tests/test_engine_service.py', 'heat/engine/service.py'], 'message': "Shut the heat-engine after all threads finished

Currently heat-engine do shutdown immediately when SIGTERM received.
At that time, a stacks in middle of processing would terminate forcefully.
It's not graceful.

This patch aims to implement graceful shutdown with following methods.

  * Close rpc connection at first for preventing new requests arrived
    after SIGTERM received.
  * Stop stack processing with graceful option.
    The graceful stop functionality is provided by oslo-incubator.
  * Then terminating process.

Change-Id: I8689b830774f7916febb59aca00979d92c0448b5
Closes-bug: #1304244
"}]
commit_message:
Shut the heat-engine after all threads finished

Currently heat-engine do shutdown immediately when SIGTERM received.
At that time, a stacks in middle of processing would terminate forcefully.
It's not graceful.

This patch aims to implement graceful shutdown with following methods.

  * Close rpc connection at first for preventing new requests arrived
    after SIGTERM received.
  * Stop stack processing with graceful option.
    The graceful stop functionality is provided by oslo-incubator.
  * Then terminating process.

Change-Id: I8689b830774f7916febb59aca00979d92c0448b5
Closes-bug: #1304244

commit_message:
Nova: custom notification and memcached options

This change is to allow settings for the common configuration options:

  memcached_servers
    Allow specification of list of memcached servers to offer
    persistence/resiliency and store ephemeral data - instead of
    using Nova in-process cache.
  notification_topics
    Allow sending notifications to multiple RPC topics.
    e.g. Monitoring and Billing
  notify_api_faults
    If set, send api.fault notifications on caught exceptions in the API
    service.

Change-Id: I01633366e6fe61aea1b9d32527a023a1dd898548

commit_message:
Agent handler should retrieve node by interfaces

In case of neutron, agent doesn't send mac
address of physical interface, it sends
mac address of bridge, in this case we
should retrieve node by list of interfaces.

Change-Id: I870ffcd9e02bc6262f73cb64e0cdbdf6ab0ad1c5
Closes-bug: #1314962

commit_message:

This commit adds the first unit tests for the verify_tempest_config
script which covers the code used to format an unversioned endpoint

breaks that section of the script off into a separate method so that

commit_message:
Bump python-keystoneclient to >= 0.8.0

Starting from python-keystoneclient 0.8.0, the preferred way to
specify authN and identity endpoints is by using auth_uri and
identity_uri settings.  Otherwise, warnings are issued. To be able to
migrate to brand new world, we need to bump to the new version where
these settings were introduced.

Change-Id: Icbb9c3af9110e405d8b44bda529ccf1b3c1ae3a0

commit_message:
Don't print duplicate messages on SystemExit

Don't log the error using LOG.error or LOG.exception and then
passing the same string to SystemExit since this will result in the
error being logged twice. Instead log the error and raise SystemExit(1).

Change-Id: I88b6632e6596a36a7168155dd4219e7d55078621

commit_message:
Updates package installs for HDP images

This patch updates several package installs for the HDP 1.3.2
  and 2.0.6 images.
Testing revealed that the version of Ambari installed on the
  HDP images was out of date, and so this patch updates the
  Ambari version to be in line wth the HDP plugin's
  requirements.
Various updates to the installed packages in order to reduce
  the startup time of HDP clusters, since these packages were
  being installed by Ambari at startup time previously.

Change-Id: I797e2d0eb30181c1be9643dea9c6d86c917cf6e5

commit_message:
Fix bad Mock calls to assert_called_once()

To actually check if a call was made, we should use
assert_called_once_with. assert_called_once is just a auto-spec'd
method and hence does not really check anything.

Change-Id: I21064dfca2a281683ee3b6ed4926f471bb74dbfa

commit_message:
Improve reliability of OSTF init hook

OSTF initialization hook will retry every
5 seconds for 250 seconds to try to set
up its database instead of trying once
and silently failing.

commit_message:
Truncate status_reason to column length

This avoids a DataError "Data too long for column 'status_reason'"
when status_reason is longer than 255 chars.

This is implemented in the class StateAware which is extended
by Stack, Resource, and SoftwareDeployment.

Change-Id: I520803e54f9045fce2dc3b6a1b5c3be5052080aa
Closes-Bug: #1312815

commit_message:
Update documentation to clarify Image Upload setting

The documentation at http://docs.openstack.org/developer/horizon/topics
/deployment.html#file-uploads states that the end user should change the
setting "HORIZON_IMAGES_ALLOW_UPLOAD = False" to disable image uploads.

This suggests that image uploads will be completely disabled, however it
will still be possible to upload images via URL.

This change adds this clarification to the documentation.

Closes-Bug: 1215921
Change-Id: Ie1cc51aaf459f9eb2881121b405fb16e762e265b

commit_message:
Use datetime object for fake network timestamps

The fake networks use a pre-serialized timestamp in str(datetime)
format which which doesn't give us the opportunity to test the
serialization code properly and isn't the format use in practice.

Use real dateime objects instead.

Full context here:

  http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2014-April/033971.html

Change-Id: I5cbe722fb59cdd326b4c75dcfea14f206d71f668

commit_message:
Allow passing environment variables to execute()

Some of the projects might need to pass environment variables
to the processes they launch. For instance, if something needs
to rely on the process' output it should be able to pass LANG="C"
in order to set the correct localization.

This patch adds a env_variables parameter to processutils.execute()
which allows to pass news variables or replace the value of the existing
ones for the process.

Closes-bug: #1304284
Change-Id: If801e11391bf7cf66518533443c3b29af53653e5

commit_message:
Make port-id and net-id keys mutually exclusive

These keys are never used together, and port-id always takes precedence
in Nova API when present. This patch makes these parameters mutually
exclusive and updates help strings accordingly.

Change-Id: I61170291468757b47b043bd81f022704dd38e3d0

commit_message:
Fix endpoint error when running keystone on apache

When running keystone in httpd, horizon could not generate the
right keystone endpoint url. Fixes this issue by retrieving the
whole path from the service_catalog or OPENSTACK_KEYSTONE_URL
and generating a new url.

Change-Id: Id8459947498127e47700d9f690d4ed4d5cadbba9
Closes-bug: #1295128

commit_message:
NSX: change api mapping for Service Cluster to Edge Cluster

NSX 4.2 GA has tweaked the naming for certain resources. Edge
Cluster vs Service CLuster is one of them.

Closes-bug: #1312822

Change-Id: Id4ddd99128c5e82e7a40c2d9e7385b272549cc3e
(cherry picked from commit 07a8751f799ede6b3d4868d8268148f21e17a47a)

commit_message:
Add retries to nailgun syncdb for docker deployment

Nailgun sometimes fails because postgres is
not ready yet when nailgun container starts.

blueprint fuel-containerization-of-services

commit_message:
Rename NotAuthorized exception to Forbidden

The NotAuthorized NovaException has an internal code of 403 which is
actually Forbidden, so rename it appropriately.

This patch doesn't change the external behavior, the status code in
responses will still be 403 but the exception is just named properly.

This is also necessary to create an actual Unauthorized NovaException
with code 401 for use in some Neutron API bug fixes for more granular
error handling from python-neutronclient.

Related-Bug: #1298075

Change-Id: I691fac2e2c797f47c04da7965d7b1c8685c74edb

commit_message:
Load engines with defined args and provided kwargs

To match the other fetch() functions, make the engine
load and run methods take in kwargs which can be used
by a specific engine if needed. Instead of the previous
passing engine args by invoke_kwds, use the invoke_args
with the specific kwargs being placed in invoke_kwds.

Change-Id: I7974ed774909de82a8b48615dfe29836ca8d809d

commit_message:
Integrate urlparse for configuration augmentation

Allow the uri passed to various entrypoints to itself
contain most of the configuration for that entrypoint
by using the RFC 3986 uri format to allow for additional
parameters to be used in configuring and selecting those
entrypoints.

Also bring over network_utils from oslo since it provides
a more compliant url splitting support.

Part of blueprint persistence-uris

Change-Id: I8e5d8584d2cac4f9b338fa155f220cdfd52bb7d9

commit_message:
Make events return by insertion order

We fixed the table by having the ID available, but the query uses an
index, so MySQL will return the rows in index order, which is not
necessarily primary key order. We need to explicitly ask that it be
returned in primary key order. This should be a free operation on MySQL.

Change-Id: I48d6260e01736fc7475c13cf736968dbf8eda206

commit_message:
Don't pass enable_snat by default in Router

The patch removes the default for enable_snat in the Router resource and
removes the value if not specified, to make it possible for non-admin
users to create routers: a policy rule in neutron forbids non-admin to
pass the enable_snat value.

It doesn't break backward compatibility as enable_snat is the default in
neutron.

Co-Authored-By: ala.rezmerita@cloudwatt.com
Closes-Bug: #1306593
Change-Id: Ib9d31f7e0a246bcaa663aaa74755526f8e31df7e
(cherry picked from commit d7836e922577f8fad4a2fba4658d4f74ed8a2e4a)

commit_message:
NSX: fix migration for networks without a subnet

In case the network is without a subnet, calling the validation
logic during the report phase leads to an error because the LSN
would have been already allocated during the migration phase.

Bypass the issue by calling the plugin directly, which is what
the validation logic does in the first place.

Closes-bug: #1313997

Change-Id: I14f77ae3b0cc147c4ea1c79e56bdd809de7c76a0
(cherry picked from commit 47e51e7521784f6a2edcfbf71a9aac0237e76e42)

commit_message:
Flavor access list titles consistent capitalization.

On the flavor access tab of the edit flavor workflow, you
can select the projects that have access to the flavor.
Currently, the left list is "All Projects" and the right
list is "Selected projects". The "p" should be capitalized
in Selected projects.

This changes "Projects" in both list titles to be capitalized.

Change-Id: Ica2958b50bd4d5dad7c1237bb2450a1c6f3e6efe
Closes-Bug: #1311715

commit_message:
Stop swift resource leaking even if an error occurs

In some test, if an error occurrs in setUpClass(), some resources
are not deleted because of tearDownClass() is not called.
This commit fixes it but doesn't touch the code of creating only one
resource without waiting for the resource creation.

 tempest/api
  +---- baremetal (unnecessary)
  +---- compute
  +---- data_processing (unnecessary)
  +---- database (unnecessary)
  +---- identity
  +---- image (done)
  +---- network
  +---- object_storage         <-- this patch
  +---- orchestration
  +---- queuing (unnecessary)
  +---- telemetry (unnecessary)
  +---- volume (done)

Partially Implements: blueprint stop-leaking

Change-Id: I69dd5bf9dbfa04e463b63f4f236fc0aa9e70e79a

commit_message:
Replace non-breaking space

Some files contained non-breaking space where normal space characters
could be used - or contained them at end of line. This patch cleans up
all places.

Related-Bug: #1314498

Change-Id: Ib45aad87796250036d5251b718c03a6f409ae66e

commit_message:
Add cmd entry point for verify_tempest_config

This commit moves the verify_tempest_config script from the tools dir
to tempest.cmd and adds a pbr entry point for the script. This means
that the script will in effect be a packaged binary for tempest.

Partially implements bp config-verification

Change-Id: I75b9743a8117d55c6c445db05eb39404b5708624

commit_message:
Add support for updating the config file

This commit adds a new flag to the verify_tempest_config.py script,
'-u' that will update the config file from values found during the
verification process.

Partially implements bp config-verification

Change-Id: I20b8bca7d3368b56da0a0496ed7aa3c1a6eacc9e
